Class Settings

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component
      • java.awt.Container
        • javax.swing.JComponent
          • javax.swing.JPanel
            • Settings
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.event.ActionListener, java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, java.util.EventListener, javax.accessibility.Accessible

    public class Settings
extends javax.swing.JPanel
implements java.awt.event.ActionListener
    The Settings class controls the contents of the JPanel used for the settings screen. Currently, this only includes the background and a button to return to the main menu.

    Variable | Type | Description
    background | Image | This Image object stores the picture used for the background of the screen. back | JButton | This JButton is used to return to the main menu. frame | Window | This Window object is given through a parameter in the constructor and is used to access methods in Window.

    Version:
    Version 2.0 May 25, 2012
    Author:
    Branson Lee, Peng Chen

    • Constructor Detail

      • Settings

        public Settings(Window frame)
        This constructor will set the reference variable frame to refer to the Window object given in the parameters. The layout will then set to be null and the background image is imported and assigned to the variable background. The back button is also created here with set location and size. Other properties of the button is also modified in the constructor.
        Parameters:
        frame - Window object that accesses Window methods later.

    • Method Detail

      • addButtons

        public void addButtons()
        This method will create the buttons needed for the main menu. The pictures used in the buttons will also be imported here as ImageIcon objects. The size, location and other properties of each button are also set here.

        The for loop goes through each button in the button array.

      • actionPerformed

        public void actionPerformed(java.awt.event.ActionEvent ae)
        This method listens for actions thrown by buttons in the panel.

        This method will set an Avatar based on the user's button click.

        Specified by:
        actionPerformed in interface java.awt.event.ActionListener
        Parameters:
        ae - This is the action event thrown whenever a button is pressed.

      • paintComponent

        public void paintComponent(java.awt.Graphics g)
        This method is overrided from the JPanel class. It is overrided to draw the Image background to the panel as well as set the opacity of all components to half so that transparencies are possible.
        Overrides:
        paintComponent in class javax.swing.JComponent
        Parameters:
        g - The Graphics instance used to draw everything.
